-- Google Says Confident Its Privacy Policy Respects European Rules
-- B y   M a r i e   M a w a d
-- 2012-10-16T10:01:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-16/google-says-confident-its-privacy-policy-respects-european-rules.html
Google Inc. is “confident” that
its privacy policy respects European law, its Global Privacy
Counsel  Peter Fleischer  said today in an e-mailed statement.  The statement comes after the company, operator of the
world’s largest search engine, was told by European Union
regulators to bolster its privacy policy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marie Mawad in Paris at 
 mmawad1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
